The paper deals with learning a distance metric from noisy constraints, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The use of smooth optimization and empirical study with UCI data sets suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
